# Flutter Architecture Guide

## Project Structure
This Flutter app follows a modular architecture with clear separation of concerns:

- `lib/main.dart` is the entry point
- `lib/core/` contains app-wide utilities and constants
- `lib/features/` contains feature-specific modules
- `lib/data/` contains models and data handling logic
- `lib/presentation/` contains UI components and state management

## Design Guidelines
- Use the defined color palette in `core/constants/app_colors.dart`:
  - Background: #0A0E1A (午夜蓝)
  - Text/UI elements: #F0F0F0 (星尘白)
  - Accent colors: #FF3B30 (炽热红), #00A9E0 (冷静蓝), #FFD60A (黄金光)
- Follow the immersive, space-themed UI with glow effects and smooth animations
- Implement responsive layouts for all screens

## Development Rules
- Use setState for state management (not Provider/Bloc)
- Use shared_preferences for data persistence
- No external fonts or local image assets
- No cached_network_image
- No account functionality
- No freezed package or part syntax

## Feature Modules
- Market: Trading pairs with interactive charts
- Signals: Sentiment analysis visualization
- Insights: News timeline with event tracking
- Settings: App configuration and information
